<br>
You setup a new hotkey bank, click and drag your primary weapon slot down to hotkey bank, and your secondary.  Then if you wish, and have a free inventory space or 2, drag those down to the hotkey area - thus you could leave your alt weapons in those free main inventory slots, and be able to swap out weapons without changing views or having to go to your inventory screen to do so.  I think you can also open bags up from a hotkey slot, so don't even need a free inventory space, just hotkey a bag where ya keep weapons. I make use of this sometimes, I have a ToD, and a tash stick I use in different circumstances, nice to be able to quickly swap out these weapons to my normal ones once their purpose is served. <p><img src="http://mtwebster.home.mindspring.com/eqpics/warlace.JPG"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ugurng.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gurng</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 69<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/5/01 1:06:40 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Weapon Switch Macro</span><hr size=1> <br>
